<p>I am confused to choose between the two methods to have a STL structure ,</p>  <p><strong>Method A:</strong></p>  <pre><code>map&lt;pair&lt;string,int&gt;,map&lt;string,map&lt;ULONG,vector&lt;string&gt;&gt;*&gt;*&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>Method B:</strong></p>  <p>Is the above advisable or having a separate maps like below,</p>  <pre><code>map&lt;pair&lt;string,int&gt;,vector&lt;string&gt;&gt; </code></pre>  <p>After querying from this parent map , then iterating the vector and query the second map</p>  <pre><code>map&lt;string,map&lt;ULONG,vector&lt;string&gt;&gt;*&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Out of the above two methods which is the optimal way and which will cause more performance overhead? </p>  <p>Update 1:</p>  <p>My target is to store the output logs in memory which has three groups.. the outermost key "pair" is parent grouping and which has it's own sub groups.. And each sub groups will have it's own groups.</p>  <p><strong>After TypeDef the Method A:</strong></p>  <pre><code>  typedef map&lt;ULONG,vector&lt;string&gt;&gt; Sub_Map2;    typedef map&lt;string,Sub_Map2*&gt; Sub_Map1;    typedef map&lt;pair&lt;string,int&gt;,Sub_Map1*&gt; Parent_map; </code></pre>  <p>For better readability </p>